[[File:Cheng Hong.jpg|thumb|right|210px|Cheng Hong]]
'''Cheng Hong''' (born 1957 in [[Zhengzhou]], [[China]]) is an English [[professor]] at the [[Capital University of Economics and Business]].

== Personal life ==
Cheng's husband is [[Li Keqiang]], current [[Premier of the People's Republic of China|Premier]] of the [[People's Republic of China]]. They have one daughter who is studying in the United States.<ref>{{cite  web |title = Cheng Hong, wife of Li Keqiang, a low-profile scholar |date = 2012-10-30 |url = http://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1072623/cheng-hong-wife-li-keqiang-low-profile-scholar |publisher=South China Morning Post}}</ref>

